result.execSummary:
The defendant William Ross Viney was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Contribute/Delinquency Child(Act=Felony) [Modifiers: Penalty-Contribute/Delinquency(Felony), Penalties for Felonies-Class "H" Felony], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.40(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Defendant to pay restitution during term of probation.
Defendant to pay court cost and cost of supervision during term of probation.

Defendant to undergo any treatment or counseling the agent deems appropriate. Defendant to maintain sobriety. Defendant to undergo risks and assessments evaluation and complete any follow up. Defendant to submit DNA sample. Defendant to have no contact with the victim or her mother, place of residence, or employment. Defendant to undergo any mental health assessment and take all if any medications prescribed.
Defendant to undergo AODA assessment and complete any follow up if needed.
Upon successful completion of probation the defendant is eligible for expungement.
